V[[File:Prof. RNDr. Petr Hájek, DrSc.jpg|thumb|Prof. RNDr. Petr Hájek, DrSc.]]\u000a'''Petr Hájek''' (born 6 February 1940 in [[Prague]]; {{IPA-cs|\u02c8p\u025btr\u0329 \u02c8\u0266a\u02d0j\u025bk}}) is a [[Czechs|Czech]] [[scientist]] in the area of [[mathematical logic]]<ref>{{cite news | url = http://www.radio.cz/cz/clanek/91701 | work = [[\u010ceský rozhlas]] | language = Czech | title = Ná\u0161 host: Matematik s hudebními sklony | date = 26 May 2007 | first = Zden\u011bk | last = Vali\u0161}}</ref> and a professor of [[mathematics]]. He worked at the Institute of [[Computer Science]] at the [[Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic]] and as a lecturer at the Faculty of Mathematics and Physics at the [[Charles University in Prague]] and at the Faculty of Nuclear Sciences and Physical Engineering of the [[Czech Technical University in Prague]]. \u000a\u000a==Academics==\u000aPetr Hájek studied at the Faculty of Mathematics and Physics of the [[Charles University in Prague]]<ref name=CV>http://www.cs.cas.cz/hajek/</ref> Influenced by [[Petr Vop\u011bnka]], he specialized in [[set theory]], [[arithmetic]], later also in [[logic]] and [[artificial intelligence]].<ref name=VIT>http://vit.ad.umel.feec.vutbr.cz/portalZS/ContentPage.aspx?PageID=b97b0db3-8760-44b8-8b8c-2794d505e0d8</ref> He contributed to establishing the mathematical fundamentals of [[fuzzy logic]].<ref name=VIT/> Following the [[Velvet Revolution]] he was appointed a [[senior lecturer]] (1993), and a professor (1997).<ref name=CV/> From 1992 to 2000 he held the position of chairman of the Institute of Computer Science at the Academy of Sciences of the Czech Republic.<ref name=CV/> From 1996 to 2003 he was also president of the [[Kurt Gödel Society]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://kgs.logic.at/index.php?id=42 | title = Our Presidents | work = [[Kurt Gödel Society]]}}</ref> \u000a\u000aLater he graduated from [[Academy of Performing Arts in Prague]], where he studied [[Pipe organ]] under Ji\u0159í Reinberger to become an organ player in a church.<ref>http://www.radio.cz/cz/rubrika/kaleidoskop/nas-host-matematik-s-hudebnimi-sklony</ref>\u000a\u000a==Awards==\u000a* 2002, Medal of the [[Ministry of Education, Youth and Sport (Czech Republic)|Minister of Education of the Czech Republic]]<ref name=CV/>\u000a* 2006, [[Medal of Merit (Czech Republic)|Medal of Merit]], third grade, in the area of [[sciences]] by [[President of the Czech Republic]] [[Václav Klaus]]<ref name=CV/><ref>http://www.hrad.cz/cs/ceska-republika/statni-vyznamenani/medaile-za-zasluhy/seznam-vyznamenanych.shtml</ref>\u000a* 2008, [[doctor honoris causa]] from [[Silesian University (Opava)|Silesian University]] in [[Opava]]<ref name=CV/><ref>http://www.slu.cz/slu/cz/pr/cestni-doktori</ref>\u000a\u000a== Papers ==\u000a* {{cite book | first1 = Petr | last1 = Hájek | first2 = Pavel | last2 = Kalá\u0161ek | first3 = Petr | last3 = K\u016frka | title = O dynamické logice | location = Praha | publisher = Academia | year = 1960}}\u000a* {{cite book | first1 = Petr | last1 = Vop\u011bnka | first2 = Petr | last2 = Hájek | title = The Theory of Semisets | location = Praha | publisher = Academia | year = 1972 | others = Trans. Jech, T. and Rousseau, G}}\u000a* {{cite book | first1 = Petr | last1 = Hájek | first2 = Tomá\u0161 | last2 = Havránek | first3 = Metod\u011bj K. | last3 = Chytil | title = Metoda GUHA: automatická tvorba hypotéz | location = Praha | publisher = Academia | year = 1983}}\u000a* {{cite book | first1 = Petr | last1 = Hájek | first2 = Pavel | last2 = Pudlák | title = Metamatemathics of First-Order Arithmetic | location = Berlin | publisher = Springer | year = 1993}}\u000a\u000a== See also ==\u000a* [[Semiset]]\u000a\u000a== References ==\u000a{{Reflist}}\u000a\u000a== External links ==\u000a* [http://www.cs.cas.cz/hajek/ Petr Hájek's former webpage]\u000a* [http://sigma.nkp.cz/F/?func=find-c&local_base=nkc&ccl_term=wau=jk01033078+or+wkw=jk01033078&CON_LNG=ENG Databases of the National Library of the Czech Republic]\u000a\u000a\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Hajek, Petr}}\u000a[[Category:Charles University in Prague alumni]]\u000a[[Category:Czech scientists]]\u000a[[Category:Mathematicians from Prague]]\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:Set theorists]]\u000a[[Category:1940 births]]\u000a[[Category:Recipients of Medal of Merit (Czech Republic)]]\u000a[[Category:Czech Technical University in Prague faculty]]\u000a[[Category:Scientists from Prague]]
